Look to Gemfile for more specs

== [INSTALLATION GUIDE] ==

Source:
git clone git@github.com:jackbit/Finfore_Stream_MongoDB.git

== INSTALL MONGODB on DEBIAN/Lenny
Import GPG Key:
$ sudo apt-key adv --keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com --recv 7F0CEB10

add this line to your /etc/apt/sources.list
deb http://downloads-distro.mongodb.org/repo/debian-sysvinit dist 10gen

and run:
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install mongodb-10gen
$ sudo gem install mongo bson bson_ext

Check if work to : http://YOURDOMAIN.com:28017/

== INSTALL PASSENGER ==
If you are installed from fresh, I use this:
http://www.rubyenterpriseedition.com/download.html

== INSTALL ALL GEMS ==
run in your project directory:
bundle install

== SETUP MPM WORKER & PREFORK ==
look docs/apache2.conf.backup

== RUN RESQUE AND REDIS ==
$ redis-server
$ resque-web -N stream

== DB STARTUP ==
$ rake db:mongoid:create_indexes RAILS_ENV="production"


